<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; "><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" size="6" color="#000066">The British School</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="6">of Guangzhou</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4"><i>Part of The British Schools Group</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#c0c0c0" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="1"><i><br></i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation}&nbsp;{!Contact.FirstName}&nbsp;{!Contact.LastName},</font></span></font></div><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">This will
be the final weekly bulletin and I would like to take the opportunity to say
farewell to those students and staff that are leaving us. It is always sad to
have to say goodbye to friends and the whole community will feel this. I would
like to thank all those students and staff and to recognise their contribution
towards making BSG the school that it is. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The longest
serving leaver in secondary is Dr. Moore. When he joined the school 4 years ago
the “secondary” school consisted of year 7+8 students alone. I know that he has
gained great personal and professional satisfaction from seeing the school grow
as it has and I would like to take this opportunity to thank him for overseeing
this development. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">I have
thoroughly enjoyed the year that has packed in so many highlights. We have seen
our first cohort of Year 11 IGCSE students through and are looking forward to
seeing many of them again as they start their A levels. I have been fortunate
enough to see our school production and hear a number of superb choir and
musical performances. We have enjoyed much sporting success in the inaugural
Pearl River Delta Conference and the Houses have battled it out in sports
competitions (if not the ill-fated swimming gala). Students have visited
Cambodia and various Chinese venues for their residentials. We have had Latin
Fest, Photographic shows, raised money for Action Aid, the Thai Floods and
other charitable concerns.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">I would
like to end by wishing all our families a happy and restful holiday. School
starts back on Monday, August 20<sup>th</sup> 2012 when we will welcome back
new and old students in our upgraded facilities. It will be a pleasure to teach
in our brand new secondary wing, see the Football and Touch Rugby teams play on
the new, large Astroturf pitch and our swimmers in the new pool. In addition,
we have been lucky enough to recruit some excellent staff, many of whom have A
level experience and will I look particularly look forward to entering this
phase of secondary development. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Again,
Happy holidays!<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Mr Iain
Ruck</font><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p><div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; "><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">The British School of Guangzhou</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; text-align: left; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">_________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: center; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: arial; font-size: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 5px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 5px; "><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: x-small; ">Member of The British School Group-&nbsp;</span><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1"><i>University of Cambridge Examination Centre - Member of The Federation of British International School of South East Asia - Member of the Conference of British International Schools&nbsp;</i>- Licensed by the Chinese Ministry of Education&nbsp;</font></span></font></div></div></div>]]></td>
